Indoors, they are fed on barley, silage and concentrates.
Calving is{staggered}to maintain a fairly steady supply of milk throughout the year. Calves are fed on mothers milk for 4 to 5 days then on powdered milk. Most of the calves are either sold privately or through local auction markets. The calves which are kept are reared to replace old and unproductive cows. No male calves are reared though some of the Hereford/Fresian cross calves are sold for fattening. All the dairy stock are{brucellosis free}and the majority are{pedigree.}
Sheep may be kept for fattening in winter, eating the turnip crop.
